		<hr />
		
		
			<div><strong>Buff - Short and Long</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>I am currently using Sokol's OceanSpray23.<br />
<br />
I would like to use RobynnMerrilin's UI_Custom_Buffwindow with OceanSpray but when I do I have some problems.<br />
<br />
1.  Only the text of the spell name is visible in the buffs window. Both the background color and spell icon are missing.<br />
<br />
2.  Cannot click off buffs..I imagine this is link to the above.<br />
<br />
Any suggestion on what to edit would be appreciated.<br />
<br />
Thanks</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br /><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="1" border="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td class="page">
	
		<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
		<tr valign="bottom">
			<td style="font-size:14pt">kitsinu</td>
			<td class="smallfont" align="right">02-09-2003 03:47 PM</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>This might have to do with the size of your window.  If the window is smaller than the width or height of the buff icons, the buff icons don't show up.  The window must be 1 pixel bigger than the width/height of the buff icon.  If you can't resize the window in the game, you will need to edit the UI_playername_##.ini file in the EverQuest directory for your character<br />
<br />
[BuffWindow]<br />
Width=180<br />
Height=326<br />
<br />
[ShortDurationBuffWindow]<br />
Width=180<br />
Height=135<br />
<br />
These numbers are approximate, but should work.  If not, add 10 to each number and tell me if there are any problems.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
